  "suggestion": "Lower harvest threshold ≠ higher efficiency. Beings waste energy checking and harvesting marginal resources. Raise threshold to filter for richer patches, reduce wasted energy cycles.; Efficiency is critically low at 0.149, dragging down overall fitness despite perfect survivalRate. Analysis: harvestThreshold across all genomes is too aggressive (0.08-0.15). Beings are harvesting at minimal resource concentrations, wasting energy on marginal gains. This creates high energy-to-reward friction. Solution: raise harvestThreshold to force beings to seek richer patches before harvesting, reducing decision cycles and movement without payoff. Also reduce explorationDrive in high-wandering genomes (Harvester and Persistence Hunter) — undirected exploration burns energy. Expected impact: efficiency should improve 40-60% with better energy ROI per harvest.",
